 Delicious Food Recipes Mussels 

00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:09.740
 500 ml milk is added to the yeast in 1 pack age yeast or 1 tablespoon dry yeast by slightly heating. 

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.720
 Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and mix until melted. 

00:00:14.220 --> 00:00:18.360
 If dry yeast is used, wait for 5-10 minutes for yeast to be activated. 

00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:21.360
 Flour up to 5 cups into the kneading dish. 

00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:23.560
 1 teaspoon of salt is added. 

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:27.280
 Slowly add dough to the dough and knead the dough slowly. 

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:38.600
 The dough is kneaded so that it is not too hard and slightly light flour is added. 

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:42.140
 Cover the stretch film with a clean cloth. 

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:44.740
 And it is left to ferment for 40 min. 

00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:49.760
 The yeast is about 2 times the dough. 

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
 The dough is taken to the floured counter. 

00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:55.940
 It is gently agglomerated to prevent it from sticking. 

00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:02.640
 It is cut into 6 pieces of approximately the same size by the decision. 

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:11.140
 Each piece is manually rounded and wrapped. 

00:01:17.980 --> 00:01:21.520
 In turn, each meringue is opened with a rolling pin in the size of a serving plate. 

00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:33.600
 After opening the first three cloths, the first one is taken with plenty of butter or margarine. 

00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:40.400
 The same process is repeated by closing the second floor. 

00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:53.280
 It is placed on the 3rd floor and pressed by hand. 

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:55.980
 The doughs are slightly opened and re-greased. 

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:09.920
 Starting from the edge of the dough is rolled in the form of rolls. 

00:02:15.540 --> 00:02:19.180
 The prepared roll is taken to the floured counter and is slightly extended by hand. 

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:27.500
 The blade is sliced ​​approximately 2 finger wide. 

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:30.860
 The thinner your roll is, the smaller your croissants will be. 

00:02:31.400 --> 00:02:33.400
 You can adjust according to your preference. 

00:02:33.940 --> 00:02:39.020
 From the first half of the dough 16 to 30 pieces of 30-35 pieces of mussels can be obtained. 

00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:42.980
 Each piece is pressed slightly by hand. 

00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:46.980
 It is placed in the middle of the inner mortar with cheese parsley. 

00:02:48.840 --> 00:02:52.460
 Covered in the form of mussels and baked in baking paper. 

00:02:53.300 --> 00:02:56.080
 Different internal mortars can be used upon request. 

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:59.100
 Egg yolk is applied on the pastry. 

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:03.620
 Cook for 10 minutes and bake in a 190 ° C oven. 

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:15.640
 After being removed from the oven, cover them with a cloth to make them softer. 

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:17.200
 Enjoy your meal. 

